  "title": "Decision aids that really promote shared decision making: the pace quickens",
  "abstract": "Decision aids can help shared decision making, but most have been hard to produce, onerous to update, and are not being used widely. <b>Thomas Agoritsas and colleagues</b> explore why and describe a new electronic model that holds promise of being more useful for clinicians and patients to use together at the point of care",
